Scope: 5 commits, ~1400 LOC, src/metrics/ package creation + 43 new tests. Arc adds Evaluation-plane Metric class hierarchy per METRICS_AND_TRUST_GATES v0.1 Draft, backing the PIVOT_CHARTER §7 P1 Metrics & Trust Layer foundation.

Files changed:
- src/metrics/__init__.py, base.py, registry.py (skeleton per commit 2b5ceb7)
- src/metrics/_comparator_wrap.py (shared Pointwise+Integrated helper + wrapper-level deviation gate fix, 27c42fe)
- src/metrics/pointwise.py, integrated.py (delegate to _comparator_wrap, 9b7aeaf)
- src/metrics/spectral.py (WARN-on-low-confidence demotion, 27c42fe; does NOT import src.cylinder_strouhal_fft — reads pre-extracted scalars from ExecutionResult.key_quantities to respect ADR-001 Contract 2)
- src/metrics/residual.py (wraps src.convergence_attestor.attest; AttestVerdict → MetricStatus mapping, 1dd91eb)
- tests/test_metrics/{test_registry.py, test_pointwise_integrated.py, test_spectral.py, test_residual.py} (12+12+9+10 tests)
- .importlinter (added src.metrics to 3 Evaluation-plane contracts)
- docs/adr/ADR-001 §2.1 (added src.metrics.* Evaluation row)

Self-estimated pass rate: 0.75.

VERIFICATION CLAIMS TO PROBE (file:line if defect):

1. Wrapper-level deviation gate correctness (src/metrics/_comparator_wrap.py around lines 90-110): When ComparisonResult.passed=True but we have value+reference_value+tolerance, we re-compute deviation and override PASS to FAIL if deviation > tolerance. Does this introduce false positives when reference_value is extracted with a different key than what comparator used internally? What if reference_values has multiple entries and the first dict key extraction picks a different scalar than comparator _compare_scalar iterated through?

2. SpectralMetric low_confidence demotion interaction with FAIL (src/metrics/spectral.py around lines 94-110): FAIL must NOT be upgradable to WARN (we only demote PASS to WARN on low_confidence). Is the guard correct? What if status is already WARN from some other path — do we re-demote redundantly or is the check idempotent? Also: is reading low_confidence from ExecutionResult.key_quantities the correct path vs a dedicated field on MetricReport upstream?

3. ResidualMetric log-path resolution priority (src/metrics/residual.py around lines 55-110): Priority order is (1) observable_def log_path override, (2) artifacts.log_path duck-typed attr, (3) dict log_path key, (4) ExecutionResult.raw_output_path with log.{solver} fallback, (5) direct Path/str. Is there shadowing risk where an older attribute takes precedence over a caller explicit override? The artifacts.log_path hasattr check at step 2 — does ExecutionResult even have that attribute? Confirm by grepping src/models.py.

4. ADR-001 plane contract compliance (.importlinter + ADR §2.1): The arc classifies src.metrics as Evaluation. SpectralMetric avoids importing src.cylinder_strouhal_fft (Execution) and reads scalars from key_quantities instead. But semantic_delegate string src.cylinder_strouhal_fft is preserved in delegate_to_module class attr. Is this hybrid approach defensible or does it indicate ADR-001 misclassified cylinder_strouhal_fft? Run: grep -rn cylinder_strouhal_fft src/metrics/ — should return only string references, no actual imports.

5. Tolerance-policy dispatch bug in registry.evaluate_all (src/metrics/registry.py L105-108): per_metric_tol = tolerance_policy.get(name, tolerance_policy) — falls back to WHOLE policy dict when no per-name entry. If the outer policy has a top-level tolerance key, every metric lacking a per-name entry gets the same override. Is this the intended semantic or a latent bug? test_tolerance_policy_without_tolerance_key_is_ignored covers one side but not the cross-pollination case.

6. ResidualMetric ATTEST_NOT_APPLICABLE to WARN rationale (src/metrics/residual.py L46-51): Mapping NOT_APPLICABLE to WARN (not PASS) so downstream TrustGate does not silently pass. Is this the right default? What if a user legitimately configures a case as reference tier (no solver log expected)? Should there be an observable_def opt-in to map NOT_APPLICABLE to PASS for such cases?

7. AttestationResult import surface (src/metrics/residual.py L37-41): imports AttestationResult, AttestorCheck, attest. Do we also need Thresholds for observable_def.thresholds overrides? Current impl only passes case_id to attest → load_thresholds(case_id). Is that sufficient for whitelist cases or do we need observable_def.thresholds inline override path for non-whitelist custom metrics?

8. Frontmatter + provenance schema stability (MetricReport.provenance dict): Report schema is ad-hoc — delegate_module, comparator_summary, tolerance_source, case_dir, log_path, attest_verdict, checks, low_confidence, strouhal_source, etc. Is the key naming consistent across all 4 metric classes? Will KNOWLEDGE_OBJECT_MODEL §1 Provenance schema (P4) need to impose structure here?

Output format: APPROVE / APPROVE_WITH_COMMENTS / CHANGES_REQUIRED with file:line findings. Write full log to reports/codex_tool_reports/dec_v61_054_p1_t1_arc_review.log.

