knowledge/gold_standards/fully_developed_plane_channel_flow.yaml:9:  reference_correlation_context: "Kim/Moser DNS provides u+(y+) curves at Re_tau=180. u_tau is a physically-realized friction velocity derived from the statistically converged wall shear in a turbulence-resolving simulation; u_tau = 1 in Re_tau=180 dimensionless form is a byproduct of that physics, not a definition."
knowledge/gold_standards/fully_developed_plane_channel_flow.yaml:13:      evidence_ref: "whitelist.yaml:133-154 declares icoFoam + laminar; Phase 7 T4 reverted simpleFoam+kOmegaSST attempt (STATE.md:327) because the swap conflicted with the laminar-Poiseuille gold ref_value kept for that solver path"
knowledge/gold_standards/fully_developed_plane_channel_flow.yaml:14:      consequence_if_unsatisfied: "A laminar Poiseuille profile projected through u+ = u/u_tau where u_tau is synthesized from Re_tau definition yields a curve that *algebraically* overlays DNS data but encodes no turbulence physics. Any PASS is a false PASS. This is the precondition that caused the EX-1-002 R-C pivot — see reports/ex1_002_cli_tests/slice_metrics.yaml §override_history."
knowledge/gold_standards/fully_developed_plane_channel_flow.yaml:23:  The Gold Standard ref_value is DNS-quality turbulent profile (Kim 1987) which
knowledge/gold_standards/fully_developed_plane_channel_flow.yaml:25:  the expected turbulent u+/y+ profile. This observable is INCOMPATIBLE with
knowledge/gold_standards/fully_developed_plane_channel_flow.yaml:27:  and finer mesh, or (2) Update ref_value to match laminar Poiseuille profile.
