knowledge/gold_standards/backward_facing_step.yaml:14:#   the declared 10% tolerance. The stored reference_values[].value=6.26
knowledge/gold_standards/backward_facing_step.yaml:29:  reference_correlation_context: "The stored reference_values[].value=6.26 is a blended engineering anchor (see header block). Le/Moin/Kim 1997 DNS at Re_H=5100 reports 6.28; Driver & Seegmiller 1985 experiment at Re_H≈37500 reports 6.26; both bracket the post-transition plateau at our whitelist Re_H=7600 well inside the 10% tolerance band. The anchor is cited as Le/Moin/Kim because their DNS is the closer-regime literature; the 0.02 numerical offset vs the stored 6.26 is treated as within-tolerance rather than as a pure-DNS claim. No tight <2% sensitivity claim is made — the plateau is qualitative, and the residual drift depends on expansion ratio (1.2 DNS vs 1.125 adapter), inlet BL state, and the 2D-empty-patch simplification of the adapter path."
knowledge/gold_standards/backward_facing_step.yaml:47:reference_values:
