knowledge/gold_standards/naca0012_airfoil.yaml:11:  Docker E2E: converged (p=9.7e-7), 224 Cp values extracted.
knowledge/gold_standards/naca0012_airfoil.yaml:12:  Gold comparison deviations ~30-50% — extracted values are near-surface cell
knowledge/gold_standards/naca0012_airfoil.yaml:13:  averages; reference values are exact surface points. Cp profile shape correct.
knowledge/gold_standards/naca0012_airfoil.yaml:16:  reference_correlation_context: "Thomas 1979 / Lada 2007 ref_values are *exact surface* pressure coefficients at the tabulated x/c stations. The adapter CANNOT deliver exact-surface values — it samples a near-surface band of cell centres and averages. A shape-faithful but value-attenuated Cp distribution is the expected outcome, and the 20% tolerance + PASS_WITH_DEVIATIONS verdict reflect this."
knowledge/gold_standards/naca0012_airfoil.yaml:24:    - condition: "Cp extraction sampling geometry aligns with 'exact surface' gold standard"
knowledge/gold_standards/naca0012_airfoil.yaml:26:      evidence_ref: "src/foam_agent_adapter.py:7068 surface_band = max(8.0*dz_min, 0.02*chord) — the extracted Cp is averaged over a ~2% chord thick band above the surface, not the exact surface. Lines 7073-7089 split into upper/lower candidates within search_envelope=0.25*chord."
knowledge/gold_standards/naca0012_airfoil.yaml:27:      consequence_if_unsatisfied: "The adapter's Cp values are systematically attenuated vs the ref (magnitudes reduced ~30-50%), while the x-station *shape* of the Cp curve remains faithful. PASS_WITH_DEVIATIONS is the honest verdict. A future R-A-style slice could add a 'cell_vs_surface' kind field to each Cp observable to make the comparator aware of the sampling difference."
