knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:9:  reference_correlation_context: "Williamson 1996 reports St≈0.164, Cd≈1.33, Cl_rms≈0.048 for Re=100 laminar Karman shedding from a 2D cylinder. u_mean_centerline gold values 0.83→0.35 at x/D ∈ {1,2,3,5} are WAKE DEFICIT = (U_inf - u_mean)/U_inf (per the per-point `description: centerline velocity deficit`), NOT raw u_mean/U_inf. The gold ref_value key `u_Uinf` is historical mislabeling; Batch B2 resolved this via documentation + extractor-self-naming (no rename; retained for back-compat with contract_dashboard + e2e tests)."
knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:14:      consequence_if_unsatisfied: "kOmegaSST over-dissipates the laminar wake at Re=100 → underpredicts St by 10-20%, Cl_rms by 30-50%. Likely contributor to the current audit fixture's `measurement.value = 4.93502e-06 U_max_approx` fallback."
knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:16:    - condition: "Domain is large enough that blockage does not bias Cd/St/u_centerline vs Williamson's unconfined anchors."
knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:24:      consequence_if_unsatisfied: "St and Cd RMS converge slowly on too-short windows; unit-tests in B2 guard by asserting ≥8 peaks in trimmed series."
knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:25:    - condition: "Strouhal extractor reflects solver physics (not a hardcoded canonical value)."
knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:27:      evidence_ref: "DEC-V61-041 retired canonical_st=0.165 hardcode. src/cylinder_strouhal_fft.emit_strouhal reads forceCoeffs FO postProcessing/forceCoeffs1/0/coefficient.dat and computes St via FFT of Cl(t). cd_mean and cl_rms emit from the same trimmed time-series."
knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:29:    - condition: "Audit fixture surfaces St as measurement.quantity (not U_max_approx fallback)."
knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:31:      evidence_ref: "ui/backend/tests/fixtures/runs/circular_cylinder_wake/audit_real_run_measurement.yaml → measurement.quantity = U_max_approx, extraction_source = key_quantities_fallback. Likely cascades from the kOmegaSST damping (St FFT finds no dominant peak, falls back)."
knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:32:      consequence_if_unsatisfied: "Compare-tab cannot surface St as primary scalar; 4-gate UI impossible."
knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:33:      resolution_plan: "DEC-V61-053 Batch B3 — phase5_audit_run.py writes St as primary; expected to succeed once laminar solver + grown domain produce physical shedding."
knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:36:      evidence_ref: "Gold values 0.83→0.35 monotonically decreasing are INCONSISTENT with raw u/U_inf (which INCREASES with x/D as wake recovers) but CONSISTENT with deficit (decreases with x/D as wake recovers). Per-point `description: centerline velocity deficit` confirms deficit; key name `u_Uinf` stays for backward-compat with test_contract_dashboard_report + test_e2e_cylinder_crossflow (rename attempted in B2 reverted — downstream blast radius too large for this DEC). Extractor src/cylinder_centerline_extractor.py self-names output keys `deficit_x_over_D_*` so its API is unambiguous; Batch B3 audit-fixture wiring maps gold.u_Uinf (treated as deficit per this description block) ↔ extractor.deficit_x_over_D_N by x_D lookup."
