knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:74:    - condition: "v_centerline reference values match Ghia 1982 Table II v(x) along the geometric horizontal centreline"
knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:76:      evidence_ref: "DEC-V61-050 batch 1 (2026-04-23) replaced the prior mislabelled block with Ghia Table II Re=100 native 17-point non-uniform x grid + exact v values (cross-verified against scripts/flow-field-gen/generate_contours.py:103-110 which had encoded the same values for the literature-reference visualization since DEC-V61-007). Measured v extracted from existing 20260421T082340Z VTK via pyvista interpolation on y=0.05 (physical y=0.005·0.1m = 0.005m, normalized y=0.5·L); no simpleFoam re-run needed — the underlying audit field is the same. See reports/phase5_fields/lid_driven_cavity/20260421T082340Z/postProcessing/sets/1024/vCenterline_U.xy and vCenterlineGold_U.xy."
knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:79:      evidence_ref: "DEC-V61-050 batch 3 (2026-04-23) replaced the prior mis-aligned block (x=0.5000, y=0.7650, icoFoam, 64800 cells) with Ghia 1982 Table III Re=100 values (x=0.6172, y=0.7344, ψ_min=-0.103423) and wired a 2D-argmin-of-ψ extractor via ui/backend/services/psi_extraction.py (integrates ψ = ∫₀^y U_x dy' along columns of a 129² pyvista resampling of the existing 20260421T082340Z VTK). Smoke test matches Ghia exactly in (x, y) and within 0.23% on ψ_min — see the psi_extraction __main__ harness. No simpleFoam re-run."
knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:85:      evidence_ref: "DEC-V61-050 batch 4 (2026-04-23) added the secondary_vortices gold block with Ghia Table III Re=100 values (BL: 0.0313, 0.0391, ψ=+1.749e-6; BR: 0.9453, 0.0625, ψ=+1.254e-5) and wired a corner-windowed ψ-argmax extractor. Codex round 1 MED #2 (2026-04-23) flagged that the current ∫U_x dy' + pyvista resampling method has ψ wall-closure residual ≈ 3.4e-3 on the 20260421T082340Z fixture — 2000× LARGER than the BL ψ_gold (1.75e-6) and 270× larger than BR ψ_gold (1.25e-5). The coordinate matches found by argmax are therefore in a noise-dominated regime, not a validated physics reproduction. `metrics_secondary_vortices.eddies[*].all_pass` is now gated on signal_to_residual_ratio ≥ 3.0, so both eddies correctly report all_pass=False on the current pipeline. TRUE satisfaction of this precondition requires either (a) a Poisson solve ∇²ψ = -ω_z with ψ=0 walls, which eliminates integration-constant drift, or (b) OpenFOAM-native streamfunction sampling at the fixture mesh — both outside DEC-V61-050 scope (→ future DEC)."
