knowledge/gold_standards/plane_channel_flow.yaml:9:  reference_correlation_context: "Kim/Moin/Moser 1987 / Moser/Kim/Mansour 1999 report the canonical u+ vs y+ profile for FULLY TURBULENT channel flow at Re_τ=180 (friction Reynolds). Re_τ=180 corresponds to Re_bulk≈5600 through u_τ·h/ν, which is why the adapter was sized at Re_bulk=5600. But that sizing alone does NOT make a laminar N-S solution turbulent — this is the crux of the disguised-incompatibility."
knowledge/gold_standards/plane_channel_flow.yaml:11:    - condition: "Flow is turbulent (required for Kim 1987 / Moser 1999 DNS u+ log-law to exist)"
knowledge/gold_standards/plane_channel_flow.yaml:13:      evidence_ref: "src/foam_agent_adapter.py:3270 — `application icoFoam` (transient PISO, incompressible LAMINAR N-S; no turbulence-transport equations). At Re_bulk=5600 a laminar N-S solution converges to the Poiseuille parabolic profile, not to a turbulent log-law. The reference u+ values (5.4 at y+=5, 13.5 at y+=30) are fundamentally inaccessible to this adapter path."
knowledge/gold_standards/plane_channel_flow.yaml:20:    - condition: "Comparator reads u_plus + y_plus correctly (ATTEST_PASS is a real pass, not an extractor artifact)"
knowledge/gold_standards/plane_channel_flow.yaml:22:      evidence_ref: "DEC-V61-036c G2 (2026-04-22) widened result_comparator key-chain to read u_plus/y_plus properly; STATE.md:1301 records the fix. But STATE.md:1292-1295 explicitly flags plane_channel_flow as the exact pattern 'ATTEST_PASS but Codex physics audit says physically FAIL — those are comparator/extractor bugs' — i.e., the comparator now reads the right key, but the values are a laminar Poiseuille profile mis-presented against a turbulent DNS reference."
knowledge/gold_standards/plane_channel_flow.yaml:23:    - condition: "y+=100 gold value (22.8) is consistent with Kim/Moser centerline"
knowledge/gold_standards/plane_channel_flow.yaml:25:      evidence_ref: "YAML header notes 22.8 'looks anomalous vs log-law ~16.4 and Moser centerline ~18.3; out of audit §5.2 scope, queued for follow-up'. Even under a hypothetical correct turbulent solver, the gold value itself is suspect."
knowledge/gold_standards/plane_channel_flow.yaml:26:  contract_status: "INCOMPATIBLE_WITH_LITERATURE_DISGUISED_AS_COMPATIBLE — laminar icoFoam at Re_bulk=5600 cannot reproduce Kim 1987 / Moser 1999 Re_τ=180 turbulent DNS u+ profile. ATTEST_PASS is a comparator-path artifact; a physics-honest verdict is FAIL. No comparator or extractor fix can bridge the gap — this is a solver-choice incompatibility. Queued for Phase 9 real-solver routing (either move to pimpleFoam + LES, or demote the case to laminar Poiseuille benchmark at a new gold)."
