knowledge/gold_standards/impinging_jet.yaml:10:  reference_correlation_context: "Cooper 1984 / Behnad et al. 2013 report Nusselt-number distribution Nu(r/d) for an axisymmetric heated impinging jet at Re=10000. Peak Nu=25 at the stagnation point comes from axisymmetric converging streamlines; a planar slice does not converge azimuthally and will under-predict the peak."
knowledge/gold_standards/impinging_jet.yaml:17:      evidence_ref: ".planning/STATE.md:1286 — impinging_jet ATTEST_FAIL via A4 solver_iteration_cap. src/plane_channel_uplus_emitter.py:53-56,86-88 records p_rgh GAMG repeatedly hitting the 1000-iter cap. The iteration-cap hit is a symptom observed in the current solver config; the root cause is likely a composite of under-relaxation choice, pressure-velocity coupling settings, thermal-boundary inconsistency, and axis-patch treatment (see precondition #1 for the axis/wedge mismatch) rather than a single tunable parameter. ATTEST_FAIL propagates to contract FAIL before comparator runs — there is no converged steady field from which to extract Nu. Root-cause audit deferred to Phase 9 solver-config review."
knowledge/gold_standards/impinging_jet.yaml:21:    - condition: "Nu extractor uses correct wall-normal heat-flux gradient (not a surrogate-quantity leakage)"
