CHANGES_REQUIRED

- [src/metrics/_comparator_wrap.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/metrics/_comparator_wrap.py:40) and [src/metrics/_comparator_wrap.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/metrics/_comparator_wrap.py:112) can turn a legitimate comparator `PASS` into a wrapper `FAIL`. `_extract_first_reference_scalar()` uses a different key set/order from `ResultComparator._compare_scalar()`, so heterogeneous `reference_values` can make the wrapper compare against a different scalar than the comparator actually used. I reproduced: `reference_values=[{'u': 2.0}, {'value': 1.0}]`, `actual=1.0`, `tolerance=0.1` gives comparator `PASS`, but wrapper `FAIL`.
- [src/metrics/registry.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/metrics/registry.py:107) leaks a top-level tolerance override into unrelated metrics. `per_metric_tol = tolerance_policy.get(name, tolerance_policy)` means `{'tolerance': 0.5, 'a': {'tolerance': 0.01}}` gives metric `b` the outer `tolerance=0.5` even though only `a` had a named override. That contradicts the documented `CaseProfile.tolerance_policy[<observable_name>]` semantics.

I verified the rest of the main claims: `SpectralMetric` does keep `FAIL` as `FAIL`, `uv run lint-imports` keeps all 4 ADR-001 contracts, and `uv run pytest -q tests/test_metrics/test_registry.py tests/test_metrics/test_pointwise_integrated.py tests/test_metrics/test_spectral.py tests/test_metrics/test_residual.py` passes all 43 tests. `ResidualMetric` log-path precedence looks like a priority/doc mismatch rather than a proven live regression in current repo shapes. Full log is appended at [dec_v61_054_p1_t1_arc_review.log](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/reports/codex_tool_reports/dec_v61_054_p1_t1_arc_review.log).


